Rhetoric and enforcement against dissent formed another thread. Florida Attorney General Pam Bondi went on national television to call pro-Palestinian student protesters \'93domestic terrorists,\'94 framing campus dissent as a security threat rather than political expression. She then warned Representative Jasmine Crockett to \'93tread very carefully\'94 about her comments on Elon Musk, accusing the congresswoman of threatening lives. The warning came not from a pundit but from a top law enforcement official, suggesting that sharp criticism of a powerful figure could be treated as incitement. In the same week, immigration officers targeted Yunseo Chung for deportation because of her protests, and masked agents arrested Rumeysa Ozturk despite a court order. Trump\'92s attacks on major media outlets fit into this pattern, casting critics as dishonest or dangerous.\
